<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC6FFCAFF29FDA01540C119" box="[225,523,558,579]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="714">COPESTYLUM COCKERELLI</emphasis>
(CURRAN, 1927)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFC6FFCAFF6CFDDB1440C026" blockId="17.[164,779,596,894]" pageId="17" pageNumber="714">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC6FFCAFF6CFDDB1655C132" box="[164,286,597,618]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="714">Puparium:</emphasis>
Anterodorsal margin of mesothorax with enlarged setae (conspicuously longer than surrounding vestiture, not spicules. Dorsal vestiture of abdomen confined to medial areas of transverse folds. Crochets entirely black. Posterior breathing tube dark brown, short, less than half as wide as puparium, AP short, only about 0.4¥ as long as TR is wide, lightly punctate, tapering but bulging out horizontally (
<figureCitation id="134E2A02FFC6FFCAFED9FCC71628C007" box="[273,355,841,863]" captionStart="Figures 58–61" captionStartId="49.[164,254,1145,1164]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,195,1115]" captionTargetId="figure-0@49.[323,1283,195,1115]" captionTargetPageId="49" captionText="Figures 58–61. Puparia of Copestylum, scanning electron photomicrographs, scales as indicated on images, 58, 59, Copestylum spinigera; 58, posterior breathing tube (prp), dorsal view width at TR = 0.87 mm; 59, prp, apical view width = 0.8 mm; 60, Copestylum cockerelli, prp dorsal view width at TR = 1.5 mm; 61, Copestylum hambletoni, prp, dorsal view width at TR = 1.45 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443512" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443512/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="714">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
). Pupal spiracles as long as AP and about 2.5¥ as wide apart as a pupal spiracle is long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
