<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFC6FFCAFF6CFBFF16F7C646" blockId="17.[164,779,1136,1311]" pageId="17" pageNumber="714">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC6FFCAFF6CFBFF1626C7DE" box="[164,365,1137,1158]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="714">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
The puparium of 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC6FFCAFD90FBFE15A2C7DD" baseAuthorityName="Curran" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[600,745,1136,1157]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="714" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cockerelli">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC6FFCAFD90FBFE15A2C7DD" box="[600,745,1136,1157]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="714">C. cockerelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from other Scutellatum group larvae considered here by the dorsal vestiture of the abdomen being confined to medial areas of the transverse folds, the entirely black crochets, and the short, horizontally bulging AP.
</paragraph>
